# Fast DDS Serialization Utilities API

## DynamicType to IDL Conversion

### Function Signature

The `idl_serialize` method converts a `DynamicType` object into its IDL representation:

```cpp
ReturnCode_t idl_serialize(
    const DynamicType::_ref_type& dynamic_type,
    std::ostream& output);
```

### Required Include

```cpp
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/serialization.hpp>
```

### Supported Annotations

According to the documentation, "The conversion to IDL only supports the following builtin annotations: `@bit_bound`, `@extensibility`, `@key`, and `@position`."

### Usage Example

Here's a practical implementation for converting discovered types:

```cpp
void on_data_reader_discovery(
    DomainParticipant* participant,
    eprosima::fastdds::rtps::ReaderDiscoveryStatus reason,
    const eprosima::fastdds::dds::SubscriptionBuiltinTopicData& info,
    bool& should_be_ignored)
{
    // Retrieve remote type information from registry
    xtypes::TypeObject remote_type_object;
    if (RETCODE_OK != DomainParticipantFactory::get_instance()->type_object_registry()
        .get_type_object(
            info.type_information.type_information.complete()
                .typeid_with_size().type_id(),
            remote_type_object))
    {
        return; // Error handling
    }

    // Build DynamicType from discovered TypeObject
    DynamicType::_ref_type remote_type = 
        DynamicTypeBuilderFactory::get_instance()
            ->create_type_w_type_object(remote_type_object)
            ->build();

    // Serialize to IDL format
    std::stringstream idl;
    if (RETCODE_OK != idl_serialize(remote_type, idl))
    {
        return; // Error handling
    }

    std::cout << "Type discovered:\n" << idl.str() << std::endl;
}
```

### Important Limitations

- Bitset inheritance handling: "The conversion to IDL of a Bitset with inheritance merges derived Bitsets with their base Bitset."
- Default value handling: "The conversion to IDL dismisses values explicitly set to their default value."

