## DynamicData DataReader with Dynamic Types

The pattern for reading dynamic data involves creating a new DynamicData instance, then using `reader->take_next_sample()` to retrieve samples with SampleInfo. The example shows:

```cpp
eprosima::fastrtps::types::DynamicData_ptr new_dynamic_data;
new_dynamic_data = eprosima::fastrtps::types::DynamicDataFactory::get_instance()->create_data(dynamic_type_);
SampleInfo info;
while ((reader->take_next_sample(new_dynamic_data.get(), &info) == ReturnCode_t::RETCODE_OK) && !is_stopped()) {
    if (info.instance_state == ALIVE_INSTANCE_STATE) {
        // Process data
        eprosima::fastrtps::types::DynamicDataHelper::print(new_dynamic_data);
    }
}
```

## Creating DataReader for Dynamic Topics

The workflow involves first creating a TypeSupport with the corresponding type and registering it into the participant, then creating the DDS Topic with the topic name and type, and finally creating the DataReader of that topic.

## Key Concepts

- Each DataReader is bound to a single Topic since its creation, which must exist prior to DataReader creation and be bound to the data type that the DataReader wants to publish. Creating a new DataReader for a specific Topic initiates a new subscription with the name and data type described by the Topic.

