I now have a complete understanding of the codebase and the FastDDS 3.4 API. Here is the full implementation plan.

---

## FastDDS Backend Implementation Plan for pj_bridge

### 1. Directory Structure

```
pj_bridge/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ include/pj_bridge_fastdds/
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds_topic_discovery.hpp     # Lower-level: participant mgmt + type discovery
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds_subscription_manager.hpp # Lower-level: DataReader mgmt + CDR extraction
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds_topic_source.hpp        # Adapter: TopicSourceInterface
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ fastdds_subscription_adapter.hpp # Adapter: SubscriptionManagerInterface
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ src/
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds_topic_discovery.cpp
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds_subscription_manager.cpp
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds_topic_source.cpp
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ fastdds_subscription_adapter.cpp
в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ main.cpp                        # CLI11 entry point + event loop
в”ңв”Җв”Җ conanfile.txt                           # NEW: Conan 2 dependencies for FastDDS
в””в”Җв”Җ CMakeLists.txt                          # MODIFIED: add ENABLE_FASTDDS block
```

### 2. File Descriptions

#### `fastdds/include/pj_bridge_fastdds/fastdds_topic_discovery.hpp`

Equivalent of RTI's `DdsTopicDiscovery`. Manages DomainParticipants, discovers remote publishers via `on_data_writer_discovery()`, resolves DynamicType via TypeObject registry, generates IDL via `idl_serialize()`.

**Class outline:**

```cpp
#pragma once

#include <fastdds/dds/domain/DomainParticipant.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/domain/DomainParticipantFactory.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/domain/DomainParticipantListener.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/subscriber/Subscriber.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/topic/TypeSupport.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/dynamic_types/DynamicType.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/dynamic_types/DynamicPubSubType.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/serialization.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/type_representation/ITypeObjectRegistry.hpp>

#include <cstdint>
#include <memory>
#include <shared_mutex>
#include <string>
#include <unordered_map>
#include <vector>

namespace pj_bridge {

struct FastDdsTopicInfo {
  std::string name;
  std::string type_name;
};

class FastDdsTopicDiscovery {
 public:
  explicit FastDdsTopicDiscovery(const std::vector<int32_t>& domain_ids);
  ~FastDdsTopicDiscovery();

  FastDdsTopicDiscovery(const FastDdsTopicDiscovery&) = delete;
  FastDdsTopicDiscovery& operator=(const FastDdsTopicDiscovery&) = delete;

  std::vector<FastDdsTopicInfo> get_topics() const;
  std::string get_schema(const std::string& topic_name) const;

  // Needed by FastDdsSubscriptionManager to create DataReaders
  eprosima::fastdds::dds::DomainParticipant* get_participant(int32_t domain_id) const;
  eprosima::fastdds::dds::DynamicType::_ref_type get_dynamic_type(const std::string& topic_name) const;
  std::optional<int32_t> get_domain_id(const std::string& topic_name) const;

 private:
  class ParticipantListener;  // inner class implementing DomainParticipantListener

  struct DiscoveredTopic {
    std::string type_name;
    eprosima::fastdds::dds::DynamicType::_ref_type dynamic_type;
    std::string schema_idl;
    int32_t domain_id;
  };

  void on_topic_discovered(
      const std::string& topic_name, const std::string& type_name,
      eprosima::fastdds::dds::DynamicType::_ref_type dynamic_type,
      const std::string& schema_idl, int32_t domain_id);

  mutable std::shared_mutex mutex_;
  std::unordered_map<std::string, DiscoveredTopic> topics_;
  // Participants are raw pointers managed by DomainParticipantFactory
  std::unordered_map<int32_t, eprosima::fastdds::dds::DomainParticipant*> participants_;
  std::vector<std::unique_ptr<ParticipantListener>> listeners_;
};

}  // namespace pj_bridge
```

#### `fastdds/src/fastdds_topic_discovery.cpp`

The `ParticipantListener` inner class overrides `on_data_writer_discovery()`. When a new DataWriter is discovered:

1. Get `TypeObject` from `TypeObjectRegistry` using `info.type_information.type_information.complete().typeid_with_size().type_id()`
2. Build `DynamicType` via `DynamicTypeBuilderFactory::get_instance()->create_type_w_type_object(remote_type_object)->build()`
3. Generate IDL via `eprosima::fastdds::dds::idl_serialize(dynamic_type, oss)` to a `std::ostringstream`
4. Store in `topics_` map

**RTI to FastDDS API mapping for topic discovery:**

| Operation | RTI Connext DDS | FastDDS 3.4 |
|-----------|----------------|-------------|
| Create participant | `dds::domain::DomainParticipant(domain_id)` | `DomainParticipantFactory::get_instance()->create_participant(domain_id, qos)` |
| Discovery listener | `NoOpDataReaderListener<PublicationBuiltinTopicData>` on builtin subscriber | `DomainParticipantListener::on_data_writer_discovery(participant, reason, info, should_be_ignored)` |
| Get type from discovery | `sample.data().extensions().type()` | `type_object_registry().get_type_object(info.type_information...type_id(), type_obj)` then `DynamicTypeBuilderFactory::create_type_w_type_object(type_obj)->build()` |
| Type to IDL | `rti::core::xtypes::to_string(type, idl_format)` | `eprosima::fastdds::dds::idl_serialize(dynamic_type, ostream)` |
| Check struct type | `type->kind() == TypeKind::STRUCTURE_TYPE` | `dynamic_type->get_kind() == TK_STRUCTURE` |
| Topic name | `sample.data().topic_name().to_std_string()` | `info.topic_name.to_string()` |
| Type name | `type->name()` | `dynamic_type->get_name()` |
| Destroy participant | `participant.close()` | `DomainParticipantFactory::get_instance()->delete_participant(participant)` |

**Key implementation note regarding type discovery**: FastDDS requires the TypeLookup service to be enabled via DomainParticipant QoS for complex types. Set `auto_fill_type_information` to true and enable TypeLookup client/server in the participant QoS:

```cpp
DomainParticipantQos pqos;
pqos.wire_protocol().builtin.typelookup_config.use_client = true;
pqos.wire_protocol().builtin.typelookup_config.use_server = true;
```

#### `fastdds/include/pj_bridge_fastdds/fastdds_subscription_manager.hpp`

Equivalent of RTI's `DdsSubscriptionManager`. Manages ref-counted subscriptions with FastDDS DataReaders.

```cpp
#pragma once

#include <fastdds/dds/subscriber/DataReader.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/subscriber/DataReaderListener.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/subscriber/Subscriber.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/topic/Topic.hpp>

#include <cstdint>
#include <functional>
#include <memory>
#include <mutex>
#include <string>
#include <unordered_map>
#include <vector>

#include "pj_bridge_fastdds/fastdds_topic_discovery.hpp"

namespace pj_bridge {

class FastDdsSubscriptionManager {
 public:
  using DdsMessageCallback = std::function<void(
      const std::string& topic_name,
      std::shared_ptr<std::vector<std::byte>> cdr_data,
      uint64_t timestamp_ns)>;

  explicit FastDdsSubscriptionManager(FastDdsTopicDiscovery& discovery);
  ~FastDdsSubscriptionManager();

  FastDdsSubscriptionManager(const FastDdsSubscriptionManager&) = delete;
  FastDdsSubscriptionManager& operator=(const FastDdsSubscriptionManager&) = delete;

  void set_message_callback(DdsMessageCallback callback);
  bool subscribe(const std::string& topic_name);
  bool unsubscribe(const std::string& topic_name);
  size_t ref_count(const std::string& topic_name) const;
  void unsubscribe_all();

 private:
  class InternalReaderListener;  // DataReaderListener subclass

  struct SubscriptionInfo {
